modules.description: This module manages dynamic, thread-local ambient state using a heterogeneous map (`Hmap.t`). It allows creating scoped bindings for typed keys, retrieving values by key, and executing functions within modified contexts. Concrete use cases include managing request-scoped configuration, temporary overrides, or contextual data in concurrent programs.

This module manages dynamic, thread-local ambient state using a heterogeneous map (`Hmap.t`), supporting scoped bindings for typed keys and value retrieval. It provides operations to bind keys within a scope, run computations in modified contexts, and access the current context's state. Use cases include handling request-scoped configuration, temporary overrides, and contextual data in concurrent programs.
